  "user_text": "The Hotel Evanstonian process begins when an order is received from a hotel guest by the room service manager.\n\nThe room service manager creates and forwards the order ticket.\n\nNext, several tasks are carried out in parallel:\nIn the kitchen, meals are prepared, while the waiter prepares the cart and non-alcoholic beverages.\nThe sommelier checks if wine is desired.\nIf yes, the sommelier fetches the wine from the cellar.\nThen, it is checked if other alcoholic beverages are desired.\nIf yes, the sommelier prepares these beverages.\n\nAll prepared items are then consolidated, and the waiter delivers the desired order to the hotel guest.\n\nAfter delivery, it is checked if there are no other orders to process.\n\nIf this is the case, the waiter debits the customer's account.\n\nFinally, the customer order is completed.",
  "output_text": "The process begins when an order is received. Once the order is received, an order ticket is created and forwarded. This initiates three parallel activities. \n\nFirst, meals are prepared. Second, a cart and non-alcoholic beverages are prepared. Third, there is a check to determine if wine is desired. If wine is desired, it is fetched from the cellar. If wine is not desired, the process continues without fetching wine.\n\nAfter checking for wine, there is another check to see if other alcoholic beverages are desired. If they are desired, these beverages are prepared. If they are not desired, the process continues without preparing other alcoholic beverages.\n\nOnce all parallel activities are completed, the order is delivered to the guest. After delivery, all items are consolidated. Following consolidation, there is a check to see if there are any other orders. \n\nIf there are no other orders, the customer's account is debited. If there are other orders, the process continues without debiting the account immediately. Finally, the process concludes."
